<paragraph id="8BBA340AD713FFD981A2FB638ED95BCE" blockId="5.[174,1219,1166,1193]" box="[174,1219,1166,1193]" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">
<heading id="D0F28366D713FFD981A2FB638ED95BCE" box="[174,1219,1166,1193]" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">H i g h - a l t i t u d e z o n e d i s t r i b u t i o n a n d s e a s o n a l d y n a m i c s o f t h e R h y s s i n a e</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBA340AD713FFD981EFFB228BA65A0E" blockId="5.[174,1232,1230,1449]" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">
During the investigations carried out in various locations of the Ukrainian Carpathians between 2009 and 2013 six species of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D713FFD98236FB0289A95A6F" authorityName="Morley" authorityYear="1913" box="[826,947,1262,1288]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Rhyssinae">Rhyssinae</taxonomicName>
, belonging to three genera, were recorded. One species was recorded for the first time from 
<collectingCountry id="F312749AD713FFD982FCFAE28E495A4F" box="[1008,1107,1294,1320]" name="Ukraine" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
. The most abundant rhyssine between 2009 and 2013 was 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D713FFD983E3FAC289D45A2F" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[751,974,1326,1352]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Rhyssa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persuasoria">
<emphasis id="B971E818D713FFD983E3FAC289D45A2F" box="[751,974,1326,1352]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">Rhyssa persuasoria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(54.76 % of the total number of specimens).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBA340AD713FFDA81EFFA828E615CEE" blockId="5.[174,1232,1230,1449]" lastBlockId="6.[166,1226,718,1385]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D713FFD981EFFA828B435AEF" authorityName="Morley" authorityYear="1913" box="[227,345,1390,1416]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Rhyssinae">Rhyssinae</taxonomicName>
species have been recorded in various high-altitude zones of the Ukrainian Carpathians (table 1). All six species are collected in the f o o t h i l l o a k f o r e s t z o n e, reaching up to 
<quantity id="4CFD99EFD710FFDA8052FD228BFE5D8E" box="[350,484,718,745]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" unit="m" value="275.0" valueMax="400.0" valueMin="150.0">150–400 m</quantity>
a. s. l. in Precarpathia and Transcarpathian lowland with mixed forests, where the main tree species are 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D710FFDA8363FD03890C5C6F" box="[623,790,750,777]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="robur">
<emphasis id="B971E818D710FFDA8363FD03890C5C6F" box="[623,790,750,777]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Quercus robur</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D710FFDA822EFD03899C5C6F" box="[802,902,750,777]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rubra">
<emphasis id="B971E818D710FFDA822EFD03899C5C6F" box="[802,902,750,777]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Q. rubra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D710FFDA829EFD0389E75C6E" authorityName="Montfort" authorityYear="1810" box="[914,1021,751,777]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pleurodontidae" genus="Caprinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B971E818D710FFDA829EFD0389E75C6E" box="[914,1021,751,777]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Caprinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D710FFDA851BFD038E645C6F" box="[1047,1150,751,776]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Oleaceae" genus="Fraxinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B971E818D710FFDA851BFD038E645C6F" box="[1047,1150,751,776]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Fraxinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D710FFDA8587FD038B345C4F" authority=", Abies" authorityName="Abies" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Picea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="abies">
<emphasis id="B971E818D710FFDA8587FD038AFA5C4F" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Picea abies</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B971E818D710FFDA81E3FCE28B345C4F" box="[239,302,782,808]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Abies</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B971E818D710FFDA803AFCE28B725C4F" box="[310,360,782,808]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">alba</emphasis>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D710FFDA80A6FCE388405C4F" box="[426,602,782,808]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sylvestris">
<emphasis id="B971E818D710FFDA80A6FCE388405C4F" box="[426,602,782,808]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Pinus sylvestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. No rhyssines were found in monocultural stands of 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D710FFDA81AAFCC38B4C5C2F" box="[166,342,814,840]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Fagus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sylvatica">
<emphasis id="B971E818D710FFDA81AAFCC38B4C5C2F" box="[166,342,814,840]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Fagus sylvatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the beech forest zone (
<quantity id="4CFD99EFD710FFDA83BBFCC289515C2E" box="[695,843,814,841]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="13.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" unit="m" value="850.0" valueMax="1300.0" valueMin="400.0">400–1300 m</quantity>
a. s. l.) in 
<collectingRegion id="49C1FAE8D710FFDA82CAFCC28E615C2F" box="[966,1147,814,840]" country="Ukraine" name="Zakarpattya" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Transcarpathia</collectingRegion>
, probably because of the absenсe of conifers here. Despite the fact that 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D710FFDA8295FCA28E415C0F" box="[921,1115,846,872]" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="B971E818D710FFDA8295FCA28E195C0F" box="[921,1027,846,872]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Rhyssella</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
associate with leaf trees there are no data about association of this genus with 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D710FFDA82CAFC838E6E5CEF" box="[966,1140,878,904]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Fagus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sylvatica">
<emphasis id="B971E818D710FFDA82CAFC838E6E5CEF" box="[966,1140,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Fagus sylvatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
