<caption id="DF7A6482D710FFDA81AFFD8A89C55DC0" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403929" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6403929" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403929/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" startId="6.[163,196,614,636]" targetBox="[185,1179,177,595]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph id="8BBA340AD710FFDA81AFFD8A8E2A5D1B" blockId="6.[163,1072,614,636]" box="[163,1072,614,636]" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">
Fig. 7. The seasonal dynamics of 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D710FFDA80D0FD8A88275D1B" authorityName="Morley" authorityYear="1913" box="[476,573,614,636]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Rhyssinae">Rhyssinae</taxonomicName>
flying in Ukrainian Carpathians during 1957–2013.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBA340AD710FFDA81AFFD7D89C55DC0" blockId="6.[163,991,657,679]" box="[163,991,657,679]" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">
Рис. 7. Сезонная динамика лёта 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D710FFDA80E6FD7D88515DC0" authorityName="Morley" authorityYear="1913" box="[490,587,657,679]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Rhyssinae">Rhyssinae</taxonomicName>
в Украинских Карпатах 
<date id="FFBB12CAD710FFDA824BFD7D899F5DC0" box="[839,901,657,679]" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" value="1957-05">в 1957</date>
–2013 гг.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BBA340AD710FFDA81D7FC628EAB5B2F" blockId="6.[166,1226,718,1385]" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">
Rhyssines were most abundant in the c o n i f e r o u s b o r e a l f o r e s t z o n e, situated at 
<quantity id="4CFD99EFD710FFDA81CBFC428B465CAE" box="[199,348,942,969]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" unit="m" value="1250.0" valueMax="1600.0" valueMin="900.0">900–1600 m</quantity>
a. s. l. in the mountainous part of the Carpathians, where the 
<emphasis id="B971E818D710FFDA8561FC438AE85C8F" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Piceetaabietis</emphasis>
community predominates. Only one species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D710FFDA8219FC2289E85C8F" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[789,1010,974,1000]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Rhyssa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persuasoria">
<emphasis id="B971E818D710FFDA8219FC2289E85C8F" box="[789,1010,974,1000]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Rhyssa persuasoria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was found in the subalpine zone, at 
<quantity id="4CFD99EFD710FFDA80A0FC0288565B6E" box="[428,588,1006,1033]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7305" metricValueMax="2.061" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" unit="m" value="1730.5" valueMax="2061.0" valueMin="1400.0">1400–2061 m</quantity>
a. s. l., known as polonynys, which are high altitude open grasslands, partly taken over by bush, mainly by 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D710FFDA8251FBE389F65B4F" box="[861,1004,1039,1064]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mugo">
<emphasis id="B971E818D710FFDA8251FBE389F65B4F" box="[861,1004,1039,1064]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Pinus mugo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D710FFDA82F3FBE28ED85B4F" box="[1023,1218,1038,1064]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Dushekia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis id="B971E818D710FFDA82F3FBE28ED85B4F" box="[1023,1218,1038,1064]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Dushekia viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D710FFDA81AAFBC38B6B5B2F" box="[166,369,1070,1096]" class="Pinopsida" family="Cupressaceae" genus="Juniperus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sibirica">
<emphasis id="B971E818D710FFDA81AAFBC38B6B5B2F" box="[166,369,1070,1096]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Juniperus sibirica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and only single 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D710FFDA833DFBC388B55B2F" box="[561,687,1070,1096]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Picea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="abies">
<emphasis id="B971E818D710FFDA833DFBC388B55B2F" box="[561,687,1070,1096]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Picea abies</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
trees, in which this species attacks its hosts.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBA340AD710FFDA81D7FBA289A55B8E" blockId="6.[166,1226,718,1385]" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">
The flight season of 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D710FFDA80B4FBA288325B0F" authorityName="Morley" authorityYear="1913" box="[440,552,1102,1128]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Rhyssinae">Rhyssinae</taxonomicName>
adults is prolonged, lasting six months, from the last third of April to the last third of September(
<figureCitation id="133E288FD710FFDA8327FB8288795BEE" box="[555,611,1134,1161]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[163,196,614,636]" captionTargetBox="[185,1179,177,595]" captionTargetId="graphics-413@6.[317,1156,187,506]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 7. The seasonal dynamics of Rhyssinae flying in Ukrainian Carpathians during 1957–2013. Рис. 7. Сезонная динамика лёта Rhyssinae в Украинских Карпатах в 1957–2013 гг." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403929" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403929/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">fig.7</figureCitation>
). Five species (except 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D710FFDA8242FB828E055BEF" baseAuthorityName="Gravenhorst" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[846,1055,1134,1160]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Rhyssella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obliterata">
<emphasis id="B971E818D710FFDA8242FB828E055BEF" box="[846,1055,1134,1160]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Rhyssella obliterata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) were collected during the first third of May. Rhyssines were most abundant during the first third of May and June. Thus 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D710FFDA802EFB428B885BAF" authorityName="Morley" authorityYear="1913" box="[290,402,1198,1224]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Rhyssinae">Rhyssinae</taxonomicName>
species are most common at the end of spring (in the foothill areas) and in the beginning of summer (in the mountainous part of the Carpathians).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBA340AD710FFDB81D7FB02886D5E6E" blockId="6.[166,1226,718,1385]" lastBlockId="7.[174,1232,175,265]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="34" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">
Flight periods of 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D710FFDA80A8FB02889A5A6F" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[420,640,1262,1288]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Rhyssa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persuasoria">
<emphasis id="B971E818D710FFDA80A8FB02889A5A6F" box="[420,640,1262,1288]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Rhyssa persuasoria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D710FFDA83B7FB0289745A6F" authorityName="Gravenhorst" authorityYear="1829" box="[699,878,1262,1288]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Rhyssa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoena">
<emphasis id="B971E818D710FFDA83B7FB0289745A6F" box="[699,878,1262,1288]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Rhyssa amoena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are from the end of spring to the end of summer; moreover, the first specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D710FFDA822FFAE28E1A5A4F" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[803,1024,1294,1320]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Rhyssa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persuasoria">
<emphasis id="B971E818D710FFDA822FFAE28E1A5A4F" box="[803,1024,1294,1320]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Rhyssa persuasoria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
emerged earlier, at the end of April, while 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D710FFDA80EAFAC288875A2F" authorityName="Gravenhorst" authorityYear="1829" box="[486,669,1326,1352]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Rhyssa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoena">
<emphasis id="B971E818D710FFDA80EAFAC288875A2F" box="[486,669,1326,1352]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Rhyssa amoena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
started flying later, in the latter third of May (
<figureCitation id="133E288FD710FFDA81A2FAA28AF45A0E" box="[174,238,1358,1385]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[166,199,1752,1774]" captionTargetId="graphics-698@6.[163,1220,1435,1733]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 8. Appearance of Rhyssinae species adults in ten-day periods of the 1957–2013 season." pageId="6" pageNumber="33">fig. 8</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D710FFDA800AFAA2881D5A0F" authorityName="Ozols" authorityYear="1973" box="[262,519,1358,1384]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Rhyssa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kriechbaumeri">
<emphasis id="B971E818D710FFDA800AFAA2881D5A0F" box="[262,519,1358,1384]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Rhyssa kriechbaumeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected only in May and the beginning of June. The flight periods of 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D711FFDB807EFF43884E5FAE" baseAuthorityName="Schellenberg" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[370,596,175,201]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Megarhyssa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rixator">
<emphasis id="B971E818D711FFDB807EFF43884E5FAE" box="[370,596,175,201]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">Megarhyssa rixator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D711FFDB8383FF4389BA5FAE" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1793" box="[655,928,175,201]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Rhyssella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="approximator">
<emphasis id="B971E818D711FFDB8383FF4389BA5FAE" box="[655,928,175,201]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">Rhyssella approximator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were shorter than for the two 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D711FFDB81EFFF238B8B5F8E" box="[227,401,207,233]" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="B971E818D711FFDB81EFFF238B295F8E" box="[227,307,207,233]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">Rhyssa</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, and lasting from May to the middle of July. 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D711FFDB82BBFF238E815F8E" baseAuthorityName="Gravenhorst" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[951,1179,207,233]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Rhyssella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obliterata">
<emphasis id="B971E818D711FFDB82BBFF238E815F8E" box="[951,1179,207,233]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">Rhyssella obliterata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected only in the end of September.
</paragraph>
